sec.p:
The prototype garment was tested by five subjects, three females and two males, aged between 25 and 45 years (average 35 years). All subjects were asked to put on the prototype garment and tightly fix the Velcro in order to ensure that there was a pre-stretch of about 2%. The subjects were then requested to manipulate their breathing pattern and keep the breathing rhythm for some minutes. The signal was recorded after a few minutes without the subjects being informed. The test persons were instructed to follow a sequence of breathing manoeuvres as below:


Breathing normally for three minutes in an upright position;

Breathing normally while reading a book for twenty minutes in a sitting position;

Breathing rapidly for one minute in an upright position;

Breathing slowly for one minute in an upright position;

Breathing normally three times and then holding the breath for approximately 10 s in the supine position (apnea simulation).
